explanation:
Agent A is correct. MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 recommends that a pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible. In the original code, under UPGRADE_SUPPORT the local variable is declared as
  struct MHD_UpgradeResponseHandle *const urh = con->urh;
which makes the pointer itself const but not the pointee. In the shown code urh is used only for NULL checks (read-only access); it is never used to modify the pointed-to object. Therefore the pointee can and should be const-qualified (for example: const struct MHD_UpgradeResponseHandle *const urh = con->urh;). Declaring the pointee const documents read-only intent and satisfies Rule 8.13. The only caveat would be if urh were used later to modify the object; in that case adding const would be incorrect. In this code no such modification via the local urh occurs, so the report of a Rule 8.13 violation is correct.
